'''Luc Rollet de Fougerolles''' (born 12 October 2005) is a professional [[Association football|soccer player]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[F.C.V. Dender E.H.|Dender EH]], on loan from [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. Born in England, he represents the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada national team]].

==Early life==
De Fougerolles began playing soccer as a 5 year old with BHFC Battersea.<ref name="auto"/> He moved to the [[Fulham F.C. Academy|Fulham Academy]] at the age of 8, and worked his way through their youth categories.<ref name="Montréalais de seconde génération, espoir de premier plan">{{Cite web|url=https://www.lapresse.ca/sports/soccer/2023-07-16/luc-de-fougerolles/montrealais-de-seconde-generation-espoir-de-premier-plan.php|title=Luc de Fougerolles: Montréalais de seconde génération, espoir de premier plan|trans-title=Second-generation Montrealer, leading prospect|language=fr|first=Justin|last=Vézina|date=16 July 2023|work=[[La Presse (Canadian newspaper)|La Presse]]}}</ref>

== Club career ==
=== Fulham ===
On 6 April 2023, he signed a professional contract with [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hammyend.com/index.php/2023/04/de-fougerolles-signs-professional-deal/|title=De Fougerolles signs professional deal|work=HammyEnd.com|first=Dan|last=Crawford|date=6 April 2023}}</ref> On 20 June 2023, he was named "Scholar of the Year" by Fulham.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2023/june/20/De-Fougerolles-Wins-Scholar-Of-The-Year-Award/|title=De Fougerolles Wins Scholar Of The Year Award|first=Ethan|last=Georgiou|date=20 June 2023|work=[[Fulham FC]]}}</ref> He was called up to Fulham's senior team for their preseason in the summer of 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hammyend.com/index.php/2023/08/de-fougerolles-delighted-with-summer-series-showing/|title=de Fougerolles delighted with Summer Series showing|work=HammyEnd.com|first=Dan|last=Crawford|date=2 August 2023}}</ref> He made his senior and professional debut with Fulham in a 3–1 [[EFL Cup]] win over [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] on 1 November 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/ipswich-town-vs-fulham/live/499633|title=Live Commentary - Ipswich vs Fulham &#124; 01.11.2023|website=Sky Sports}}</ref>

On 11 July 2025, de Fougerolles signed a contract extension with Fulham, keeping him at the club until 2029.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-11 |title=New contract for Luc |url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2025/july/11/new-contract-for-luc/ |access-date=2025-08-11 |website=Fulham FC}}</ref>

==== Loan to Dender EH ====
On 30 July 2025, it was announced that de Fougerolles had joined [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[F.C.V. Dender E.H.|Dender EH]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-30 |title=F.C.V. Dender loan for De Fougerolles |url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2025/july/30/dender-loan-for-de-fougerolles/ |access-date=2025-08-11 |website=Fulham FC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Dunlop |first=Brendan |date=2025-07-30 |title=CanMNT defender Luc de Fougerolles joins Belgium's FCV Dender EH on loan from Fulham |url=https://canadiansoccerdaily.com/2025/07/30/canmnt-defender-luc-de-fougerolles-joins/ |access-date=2025-08-11 |website=Canadian Soccer Daily |language=en}}</ref> He made his debut for Dender on 2 August 2025, starting the match against [[Standard Liège]] and playing 76 minutes.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Live Commentary - S Liege vs Dender {{!}} 02.08.2025 |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/standard-liege-vs-fcv-dender-eh/live/532295 |access-date=2025-08-11 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
De Fougerolles was born in England to a Canadian father and an Iranian-born English mother.<ref name="auto"/>

In October 2023, de Fougerolles accepted a call-up to the senior [[Canadian men's national soccer team|Canada]] side ahead of a friendly against [[Japan national football team|Japan]] in [[Niigata (city)|Niigata]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/canmnt-announces-23-man-squad-for-friendly-vs-japan|date=5 October 2023|title=Biello names CanMNT squad: Highlights from press conference ahead of 'audition' friendly vs. Japan|work=[[Canadian Premier League]]}}</ref> He made his debut for Canada as a late substitute against [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] in their [[2024 Copa América qualifying play-offs|2024 Copa América qualifying play-off]] on 23 March 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canpl.ca/article/recap-canmnt-qualify-for-2024-copa-america-with-close-win-vs-trinidad-tobago|first=Charlie|last=O'Connor-Clarke|work=[[Canadian Premier League]]|title=RECAP: CanMNT qualify for 2024 Copa América with close win vs. Trinidad & Tobago|date=23 March 2024}}</ref> In June 2024, de Fougerolles was named to Canada's squad for the [[2024 Copa América]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/canmnt-announce-2024-copa-america-roster/|title=CANMNT ANNOUNCE 2024 COPA AMÉRICA ROSTER|date=15 June 2024|work= [[Canadian Soccer Association]]}}</ref> and was named to the starting XI for the 3rd place game against Uruguay.{{citation needed|date=January 2026}}

In July 2025, de Fougerolles was called up to represent Canada at the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onesoccer.ca/a/canmnt-announce-2025-conacaf-gold-cup-squad-roster-canada-soccer|date=July 5, 2025|title=CanMNT name full-strength squad for 2025 Concacaf Gold Cup|first=Mitchell|last=Tierney}}</ref> At the end of the year, he was named the [[Canada Soccer Player of the Year|Canada Soccer Young Player of the Year]] for 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/olivia-chisholm-and-luc-de-fougerolles-named-canada-soccers-2025-young-players-of-the-year/|title=Olivia Chisholm and Luc De Fougerolles named Canada Soccer’s 2025 Young Players of the Year|date=17 December 2025|work=[[Canadian Soccer Association]]}}</ref> In May 2026, de Fougerolles was named to Canada's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://northerntribune.ca/world-cup-2026-canada-squad/|first=John|last=Jacques|date=May 29, 2026|title=Here’s The Canada World Cup Roster|work=Northern Tribune}}</ref>

==Playing style==
De Fougerolles is a versatile player who can be deployed as [[Full-back (association football)|full-back]], [[centre-back|center-back]] or [[midfielder]]. He demonstrates proficiency in one-on-one defending, a technical first touch, and explosive movement, which allows him to contribute to ball progression from the back. He is also noted for his composure during build-up play and his mental resilience.<ref name="Meet the Canadian youngster">{{Cite web|url=https://onesoccer.ca/a/who-is-luc-de-fougerolles-meet-the-canadian-youngster-turning-heads-at-fulham-this-summer|title=Who is Luc De Fougerolles? Meet the Canadian youngster turning heads at Fulham this summer|work=[[OneSoccer]]|first=Raine|last=Ristic|date=17 August 2023}}</ref>

